    cover: "/blog/meaning.jpg",
    content: "In the summer of some year, around a time which none have heard of, and in the amidst of unrecognizable patterns, you existed.\n\nThere, you stood, observing nothingness that filled space-time around you, a full nothingness, spoiling the peace of a far-away stream.Clarity reached you, and you questioned reality as it showed up naked, in its truest form.\n\nWhat is reality?\n\nyou screamed.\n\nWhere do I stand, as earth around me falls?\n\nWhat is the meaning behind it all?Clarity is like a switch, but once turned on, it cannot be turned off, and once you question the meaning of it, the meaning of 128 chemical compounds creating the so called observable universe, you lose yourself in a stream of thoughts, leading to absolute drowning.We are all drowning, some in the filthy swamps of their ideologies, others in their own creativity, and so you question of the worthiness of drowning in a stream of questions, and whether it’ll lead to reality.Reality is often disappointing though, and life, is often meaningless in a meaningful way, that the very thing that grants it meaning, steals it away.\n\nWe spend a lifetime searching for meaning, ignoring the fact that trying to reach such meaning, makes life meaningless, that the quest of meaning is meaningless, because meaning doesn’t exist.\n\nThe paradox of meaning, is that for a meaning to exist, we shall surrender for the idea of existence of a God to grant earth that absolute meaning, and in surrendering towards the idea of a God, we assure that this meaning is not ours, but to a greater deity (supposedly existing).The stream of meaning leads to the caves of darkness, of losing one’s interest in this blue dot, and in knowing that this life is ordered by chaos, and that all of our pain, sorrow, happiness, and absurd, is inevitably fading away.\n\nKnowing that absurdity rules our 80 years of growth, and that there are no exits.\n\nWe are surrounded by darkness of thoughts, and the our biggest survival strategy, is blinding ourselves.To not see the absurd, is to deny its existence, and to grant meaning to life, is to deny its reality.My quest of meaning ends here, with this short blog, for it’s too consuming, too hard for me to handle, that it’s not worth the trouble, and that in the long run, life itself is not worth the trouble, that we are a cosmic dust, ruled by absolute chaos, searching for a thing in nothing, a blinded civilization, streaming into its own destiny, and until then, you’ll be here, in a stream, with a blindfold, protecting you from the absurd, inside of you."
